# Rules Orchestrator

This is the central orchestrator for all project rules. All rules are organized by category below. When working on a task, refer to the relevant rules for guidance.

## Core Engineering Principles

- **[Software Engineering Principles](mdc:.cursor/rules/software-engineering-principles.mdc)**: Expert software engineering principles, architectural thinking, and KISS & DRY principles. Use when making architectural decisions, designing systems, or writing code.

## Code Quality & Style

- **[Code Style & Formatting](mdc:.cursor/rules/code-style-formatting.mdc)**: Code style and formatting standards for consistent, readable code. Use when writing code to ensure consistent formatting, naming conventions, and code organization.

- **[TypeScript Best Practices](mdc:.cursor/rules/typescript-best-practices.mdc)**: TypeScript best practices for type safety, code quality, and maintainability. Use when writing TypeScript code to ensure proper typing and type safety.

- **[Refactoring Guidelines](mdc:.cursor/rules/refactoring-guidelines.mdc)**: Guidelines for safe, effective code refactoring. Use when improving code structure, removing duplication, or addressing technical debt.

## Next.js & React

- **[Next.js App Router](mdc:.cursor/rules/nextjs-app-router.mdc)**: Comprehensive Next.js App Router guidelines for Server Components, Client Components, routing, data fetching, and caching. Use when building Next.js applications.

- **[State Management](mdc:.cursor/rules/state-management.mdc)**: State management patterns for React applications using Zustand and nuqs. Use when deciding between local state, global state, or URL state.

- **[Custom i18n](mdc:.cursor/rules/i18n-custom.mdc)**: Guidelines for custom internationalization implementation in Next.js App Router. Use when working with dictionary JSON files, locale routing, middleware, and type-safe translations.

- **[React Hook Form](mdc:.cursor/rules/react-hook-form.mdc)**: Guidelines for using react-hook-form with Next.js App Router, Zod validation, and Server Actions. Use when building forms, handling form state, validation, and form submission.

- **[Tailwind CSS](mdc:.cursor/rules/tailwind-css.mdc)**: Guidelines for using Tailwind CSS with Next.js App Router. Use when styling components, configuring Tailwind, optimizing performance, and implementing responsive designs.

## AI & Machine Learning

- **[AI SDK](mdc:.cursor/rules/ai-sdk.mdc)**: Guidelines for using the AI SDK by Vercel for building AI-powered applications. Use when implementing text generation, structured outputs, tool calling, chat interfaces, or AI agents.

