## Quick Reference by Task Type

### When Creating a New Feature
1. Review **[Software Engineering Principles](mdc:.cursor/rules/software-engineering-principles.mdc)** for architectural decisions
2. Follow **[Code Style & Formatting](mdc:.cursor/rules/code-style-formatting.mdc)** for consistency
3. Use **[Next.js App Router](mdc:.cursor/rules/nextjs-app-router.mdc)** for Next.js-specific patterns
4. Use **[Custom i18n](mdc:.cursor/rules/i18n-custom.mdc)** for internationalization
5. Apply **[State Management](mdc:.cursor/rules/state-management.mdc)** for state decisions
6. Follow **[Security Guidelines](mdc:.cursor/rules/security-guidelines.mdc)** for security
7. Use **[Data Validation](mdc:.cursor/rules/data-validation.mdc)** for input validation
8. Use **[React Hook Form](mdc:.cursor/rules/react-hook-form.mdc)** for form handling
9. Write tests following **[Testing Guidelines](mdc:.cursor/rules/testing-guidelines.mdc)**

### When Working with Database
1. Follow **[Database Design](mdc:.cursor/rules/database-design.mdc)** for schema design
2. Use **[Create Migration](mdc:.cursor/rules/create-migration.mdc)** for migrations
3. Use **[Create DB Functions](mdc:.cursor/rules/create-db-functions.mdc)** for functions
4. Use **[Create RLS Policies](mdc:.cursor/rules/create-rls-policies.mdc)** for security
5. Follow **[Postgres SQL Style Guide](mdc:.cursor/rules/postgres-sql-style-guide.mdc)** for SQL formatting

### When Building UI Components
1. Follow **[Don't Make Me Think](mdc:.cursor/rules/dont-make-me-think.mdc)** for UX principles
2. Reference **[Design Inspirations](mdc:.cursor/rules/design-inspirations.mdc)** for design patterns and visual style
3. Use **[Use Design System](mdc:.cursor/rules/use-design-system.mdc)** for design system components
4. Follow **[Tailwind CSS](mdc:.cursor/rules/tailwind-css.mdc)** for styling patterns and optimization
5. Follow **[Animation Principles](mdc:.cursor/rules/animation-principles.mdc)**, **[Animation Patterns](mdc:.cursor/rules/animation-patterns.mdc)**, and **[Framer Motion Guide](mdc:.cursor/rules/animation-framer-motion.mdc)** for implementing animations and transitions
6. Follow **[Web Interface Guidelines](mdc:.cursor/rules/web-interface-guidelines.mdc)** for interactions and accessibility
7. Apply **[Performance Optimization](mdc:.cursor/rules/performance-optimization.mdc)** for performance

### When Debugging or Fixing Issues
1. Check **[Error Handling & Logging](mdc:.cursor/rules/error-handling-logging.mdc)** for error patterns
2. Use **[Monitoring & Observability](mdc:.cursor/rules/monitoring-observability.mdc)** for logging
3. Review **[Security Guidelines](mdc:.cursor/rules/security-guidelines.mdc)** for security issues

### When Refactoring
1. Follow **[Refactoring Guidelines](mdc:.cursor/rules/refactoring-guidelines.mdc)** for safe refactoring
2. Ensure tests are in place per **[Testing Guidelines](mdc:.cursor/rules/testing-guidelines.mdc)**
3. Maintain code style per **[Code Style & Formatting](mdc:.cursor/rules/code-style-formatting.mdc)**

### When Building AI Features
1. Follow **[AI SDK](mdc:.cursor/rules/ai-sdk.mdc)** for AI SDK patterns and best practices
2. Use **[Data Validation](mdc:.cursor/rules/data-validation.mdc)** for validating structured outputs with Zod
3. Follow **[Error Handling & Logging](mdc:.cursor/rules/error-handling-logging.mdc)** for error handling in AI operations
4. Apply **[Security Guidelines](mdc:.cursor/rules/security-guidelines.mdc)** for securing API keys and user inputs
5. Use **[Next.js App Router](mdc:.cursor/rules/nextjs-app-router.mdc)** for API routes and Server Components
6. Follow **[Performance Optimization](mdc:.cursor/rules/performance-optimization.mdc)** for streaming and response optimization

